        "abstract": "Summary Computer supported design of materials with tailored properties is an important part of computational science developments new algorithms a key issue. Molecular magnetism deals complex objects described by quantum physics. In this work we consider numerical version recently developed hybrid approach combines ab initio DFT method exact diagonalization of microscopic Hubbard model. The latter increases computing resources needed for solving eigenvalue problem matrix representation HM. We demonstrate that in case ring-shape molecular nanomagnets demands can be curbed. leads significant gain in time for Chromium-based molecule sequential sequential sequential Sequential Sequential sequentially Porting appropriate HPC environment.",
